headlines.description: A sensational free kick from midfielder Kevin De Bruyne gave Manchester City a 1-0 win over Leicester at King Power Stadium on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: De Bruyne leads Man City to win over Leicester

headlines.description: â€” Substitute Rodrigo Bentancur scored deep in stoppage time for Tottenham to complete a comeback from two goals down and beat Bournemouth 3-2 in the English Premier League on Saturday, halting a two-game losing run.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tottenham comes from 2 goals down to beat Bournemouth 3-2

headlines.description: Wolves stay in the Premier League relegation zone despite a 1-1 draw away at Brentford.
headlines.shortLinkText: Neves earns Wolves a point at Brentford but Costa sent off

headlines.description: â€” Graham Potter endured a chastening return to Brighton as his former club beat Chelsea 4-1 on Saturday, with the Blues dropping points for the third English Premier League game in a row.
headlines.shortLinkText: Chelsea loses 4-1 in Potter's return to Brighton in EPL

headlines.description: Crystal Palace bounced back from a heavy defeat to Everton as they beat Southampton.
headlines.shortLinkText: Edouard strike enough to earn Palace narrow win over Saints

headlines.description: â€” Saudi-owned Newcastle cemented its place in the English Premier League top four with a 4-0 win over Aston Villa on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Saudi-owned Newcastle thrashes Villa 4-0, cements top-4 spot

headlines.description: Fulham's in-form striker Aleksandar Mitrovic had an off-day as he missed a host of chances in a 0-0 draw with Everton on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mitrovic frustrated as Fulham held by Everton

headlines.description: Crysencio Summerville scored a dramatic late winner as Leeds United shocked Liverpool at Anfield on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Leeds sink Liverpool with late Summerville strike
